biobloom
------------------------------------------
BioBloom Tools (BBT) provides the means to create filters for a given reference
and then to categorize sequences. This methodology is faster than alignment but
does not provide mapping locations. BBT was initially intended to be used for
pre-processing and QC applications like contamination detection, but is
flexible to accommodate other purposes. This tool is intended to be a pipeline
component to replace costly alignment steps.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.0-0.477.gd5dcb484c705
  libgcc1-11.4.0-1
  libgomp1-11.4.0-1
  libsdsl3-2.1.1-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.4.0-1
  zlib0-1.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.41-3
  cygport-0.36.7-1
  gcc-core-11.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.4.0-1
  libboost-devel-1.66.0-1
  libsdsl-devel-2.1.1-1bl1
  make-4.4.1-2
  sparsehash-2.0.4-1bl1
  zlib-devel-1.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/bcgsc/biobloom

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/bcgsc/biobloom.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack biobloom-2.3.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./biobloom-2.3.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/biobloom-2.3.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/biobloom-2.3.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

